Real-time Laptop Performance Monitor Documentation
Overview
This Python script provides a real-time dashboard for monitoring system performance. It displays key metrics such as CPU usage, memory consumption, disk utilization, network I/O, and top processes. The tool is designed for developers, system administrators, and power users who want quick visibility into their laptopâ€™s health without installing heavy monitoring software.

Features
CPU Monitoring: Tracks usage percentage, core count, and frequency.

Memory Monitoring: Shows RAM usage, available memory, and swap statistics.

Disk Usage: Reports usage per partition, including free and used space.

Network I/O: Displays bytes sent/received, packets, and error counts.

Process Monitoring: Lists top 5 processes by CPU usage with memory footprint.

System Info: Provides hostname, boot time, and uptime.

Interactive Dashboard: Refreshes every few seconds with a clean console view.

Architecture
The script is built around the PerformanceMonitor class, which organizes functionality into modular methods:

Initialization: Sets refresh interval and start time.

Data Collection: Uses psutil to gather CPU, memory, disk, network, and process info.

Display: Clears the console and prints a formatted dashboard.

Loop: Continuously updates the dashboard until interrupted.

Key Methods
Method	Purpose
get_cpu_info	Returns CPU usage %, core count, and frequency.
get_memory_info	Provides RAM and swap usage details.
get_disk_info	Reports disk usage for all partitions.
get_network_info	Displays network traffic and errors.
get_process_info	Lists top N processes by CPU usage.
get_system_info	Shows hostname, boot time, and uptime.
display_dashboard	Prints all collected data in a formatted dashboard.
start	Runs the monitoring loop until interrupted.
Usage
Requirements
Python 3.7+

psutil library (pip install psutil)

Run the Script
bash
python performance_monitor.py
Output Example
Code
